=head1 NAME

pts_capablities - Display ptserver capabilities

=head1 SYNOPSIS

=for html
<div class="synopsis">

B<pts capabilities>
    S<<< [B<-cell> <I<cell name>>] >>> [B<-noauth>] [B<-localauth>]
    [B<-force>] [B<-auth>] [B<-rxgk> I<level>] [B<-help>]
    [B<-encrypt>] S<<< [B<-config> <I<config directory>>] >>>

=for html
</div>

=head1 DESCRIPTION

The B<pts capabilities> command displays the protocol capability bits
advertised by the ptserver.

=head1 OUTPUT

For each capability advertised by the ptserver, B<pts capabilities> prints the
index of the capability integer, the bit of the capability (in hexadecimal),
and a short description of that capability.

=head1 EXAMPLES

    % pts capabilities
    ptserver capabilities:
      capability[0] 0x00000001 = authenticated name mapping
      capability[0] 0x00008000 = unknown
      capability[1] 0x00000001 = unknown

